The "ESP8266 Core for Arduino" board manager, available in the Arduino IDE, provides a feature to display the free and maximum stack size. 

To enable this feature, include the following code at the beginning of your sketch:
```c++
extern "C" {
  #include "user_interface.h"
}
```
Then, you can use the following functions to retrieve the information:
```c++
  uint32_t freeStack = system_get_free_heap_size();
  uint32_t maxStack = system_get_free_heap_size();
  Serial.print("Free Stack Size: ");
  Serial.print(freeStack);
  Serial.println(" bytes");
  Serial.print("Max Stack Size: ");
  Serial.print(maxStack);
  Serial.println(" bytes");
```
By printing the values obtained from `system_get_free_heap_size()` function, you can see the free stack size and the maximum stack size in bytes in the Serial Monitor of the Arduino IDE.

